                               throws edu.harvard.integer.common.exception.IntegerException

      • discoveryError

        void discoveryError(edu.harvard.integer.common.discovery.DiscoveryId id,
                  edu.harvard.integer.common.exception.ErrorCodeInterface errorCode,
                  edu.harvard.integer.common.type.displayable.DisplayableInterface[] args)
        This method is called by the discovery process to report an error that occurred during discovery. The error will be logged by the discovery service.
        Parameters:
        id - . DiscoveryId of the instance of a discovery that had an error.
        errorCode - . Error code that describes the error.
        args - . Arguments to the error message.

      • discoveryServiceElementNoResponse

        void discoveryServiceElementNoResponse(edu.harvard.integer.common.topology.ServiceElement serviceElement,
                                     java.lang.String ipAddress)
        This method is called when a service element (device) does not respond the query from the discovery process. The service element will then be marked as not reachable and an event will be generated.
        Parameters:
        serviceElement - . The service element that did not respond to the discovery process request.
        ipAddress - . Address that the discovery process used to query the device.
